:"CODE";s:37:"intracytoplasmic-sperm-injection-icsi";s:12:"PREVIEW_TEXT";s:143:"Egg fertilization method that includes injection of one thoroughly selected sperm into egg cytoplasm with the help of special micro instruments";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:1383:"<h2>How is&nbsp;ICSI different from IVF?</h2>
<p>
	 The key difference between IVF and ICSI is&nbsp;how the sperm fertilizes the egg. In&nbsp;IVF, the egg and sperm (of&nbsp;which there are many) are left in&nbsp;a&nbsp;laboratory dish to&nbsp;fertilize on&nbsp;their own. IVF is&nbsp;more often used for female infertility. ICSI allows making embryos by&nbsp;fertilizing one egg with a&nbsp;single thoroughly selected sperm. This increases the chances for conception. The protocol is&nbsp;indicated to&nbsp;overcome severe male infertility even in&nbsp;the cases of&nbsp;vas deferens disorders —active sperm cells are retrieved directly from testicles by&nbsp;means of&nbsp;aspiration procedure.
</p>
<h2>In&nbsp;what cases is&nbsp;ICSI perofrmed?</h2>
<p>
	 Intracytoplasmic sperm injection is&nbsp;recommended in&nbsp;the following cases:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>few or&nbsp;absence of&nbsp;sperm cells in&nbsp;the ejaculate;</li>
	<li>low motility of&nbsp;sperm cells;</li>
	<li>antisperm antibodies in&nbsp;a&nbsp;female partner;</li>
	<li>too thick zona pellucida;</li>
	<li>more than two IVF failures in&nbsp;the history.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 In&nbsp;the International Centre for Reproductive Medicine in&nbsp;Saint-Petersburg, our qualified specialists will perform ICSI for a&nbsp;reasonable price and will help you to&nbsp;give birth to&nbsp;a&nbsp;healthy baby.
</p>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:61:"/services/ivf-programs/intracytoplasmic-sperm-injection-icsi/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"188";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:662:"&lt;p&gt;ICSI is&nbsp;a&nbsp;procedure in&nbsp;which a&nbsp;single immotile sperm cell is&nbsp;injected directly into the cytoplasm of&nbsp;a&nbsp;mature and ready for fertilization egg. The procedure is&nbsp;performed within an&nbsp;IVF cycle. Egg fertilization occurs outside a&nbsp;female body. After the successful ICSI procedure, the embryo is&nbsp;placed into the uterus for its further development. Pregnancy is&nbsp;achieved in&nbsp;70% of&nbsp;cases. Before it&nbsp;was believed that this method of&nbsp;fertilization increases the risks of&nbsp;genetic mutations in&nbsp;the fetus but numerous research studies did not confirm the assumption.&lt;/p&gt;";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}s:31:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:428";s:21:"PROPERTY_STAGES_VALUE";a:0:{}s:26:"PROPERTY_SPECIALISTS_VALUE";a:7:{i:0;s:2:"50";i:1;s:2:"28";i:2;s:2:"63";i:3;s:2:"65";i:4;s:1:"4";i:5;s:2:"55";i:6;s:2:"10";}s:26:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_FULL_VALUE";s:10:"55 000 ₽";s:29:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_FULL_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:431";s:33:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";s:28:"Medications are not included";s:36:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:432";s:26:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_FULL_VALUE";N;s:29:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_FULL_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:433";s:33:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";N;s:36:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:434";s:23:"PROPERTY_CURRENCY_VALUE";N;s:26:"PROPERTY_CURRENCY_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:435";s:29:"PROPERTY_SHOW_ON_PRICES_VALUE";N;s:32:"PROPERTY_SHOW_ON_PRICES_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:436";s:28:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_ACTION_VALUE";N;s:31:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_ACTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:437";s:28:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_ACTION_VALUE";N;s:31:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_ACTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:438";s:28:"PROPERTY_PRICE4_ACTION_VALUE";N;s:31:"PROPERTY_PRICE4_ACTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"3921:59