:"price2Formatted";s:9:"6 000 ₽";s:18:"price2OldFormatted";b:0;s:15:"price3Formatted";N;s:18:"price3OldFormatted";b:0;s:15:"price4Formatted";N;s:18:"price4OldFormatted";b:0;s:8:"currency";b:0;s:5:"text1";s:0:"";s:5:"text2";s:0:"";s:5:"text3";s:0:"";s:10:"advantages";a:0:{}s:13:"disadvantages";a:0:{}s:12:"serviceTypes";O:29:"Illuminate\\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:0:{}}s:6:"action";b:0;}i:3933;a:86:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"3933";s:4:"NAME";s:22:"Obstetric Consultation";s:4:"CODE";s:22:"obstetric-consultation";s:12:"PREVIEW_TEXT";s:0:"";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:2585:"<p>
	 A&nbsp;pregnant woman should be&nbsp;very careful about her health as&nbsp;it&nbsp;effects not only her life but also the health and life of&nbsp;her future baby. Therefore, it&nbsp;is&nbsp;critically important for a&nbsp;pregnant woman to&nbsp;be&nbsp;under the care of&nbsp;a&nbsp;dedicated specialist.
</p>
<p>
	 During your pregnancy, we&nbsp;will perform full medical examination and offer consultations of&nbsp;an&nbsp;obstetrician as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;doctors specialized in&nbsp;other areas if&nbsp;needed. You can call&nbsp;us or&nbsp;use our <a href="#contactus" data-modal-open="">contact form</a> to&nbsp;make your first appointment.
</p>
<h2>How often should you see your obstetrician?</h2>
<p>
	 If&nbsp;there are no&nbsp;specific problems, it&nbsp;will be&nbsp;enough to&nbsp;visit an&nbsp;obstetrician in&nbsp;accordance with the standard schedule of&nbsp;visits and do&nbsp;the required tests as&nbsp;administered by&nbsp;our doctor. The earlier your first appointment&nbsp;is, the better it&nbsp;is&nbsp;for you and your future baby. Please do&nbsp;not postpone your first visit to&nbsp;the clinic. Feeling confident in&nbsp;your and your baby’s state will positively influence your emotional condition and will help to&nbsp;avoid the unnecessary worries. If&nbsp;anything goes wrong, our doctor will see the problem at&nbsp;its early stage and will react immediately.
</p>
<h3>What to&nbsp;expect from a&nbsp;visit to&nbsp;your obstetrician?</h3>
<p>
	 At&nbsp;the initial consultation, our obstetrician will ask questions about your general health, examine you, and refer to&nbsp;the narrow specialists if&nbsp;required. Please get prepared for your first appointment&nbsp;— try to&nbsp;remember and write down some important information:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>the first date of&nbsp;your latest period, </li>
	<li>any reproductive illnesses or&nbsp;gynecologic surgeries you might have had before, your previous pregnancies and deliveries, </li>
	<li>possible inherited and chronic diseases.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 Please, use our <a href="#contactus" data-modal-open="">contact form</a> to&nbsp;make an&nbsp;appointment. Our International Manager will contact you to&nbsp;offer convenient date and time. You can also make an&nbsp;appointment for the online consultation. However, please, remember that an&nbsp;online consultation cannot be&nbsp;equal to&nbsp;actually seeing a&nbsp;doctor. If&nbsp;you feel not very well or&nbsp;any test results are not within the normal range, please visit the doctor as&nbsp;soon as&nbsp;possible.
</p>
