	 Urologist-andrologist is&nbsp;a&nbsp;doctor specialized in&nbsp;urinary and male reproductive systems diseases. Male infertility, prostate disorders, diagnosis and treatment of&nbsp;sexually transmissible infections, male sexual pathologies, erectile dysfunctions and ejaculation problems are the areas of&nbsp;this doctor’s expertise.
</p>
<p>
	 A&nbsp;man is&nbsp;in&nbsp;need of&nbsp;Urology Consultation if&nbsp;his female partner cannot get pregnant despite having regular unprotected sex for a&nbsp;year. The reason might be&nbsp;in&nbsp;male infertility. It&nbsp;is&nbsp;also necessary to&nbsp;see a&nbsp;doctor if&nbsp;you experience the following problems:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Urination disorders (frequent and/or painful urination, urine retention)</li>
	<li>Abdominal, pelvic or&nbsp;back pain.</li>
	<li>Pain, burning and/or itching in&nbsp;the genital area.</li>
	<li>Discomfort and pain before, during and/or after sexual intercourse.</li>
	<li>Penile discharge of&nbsp;unusual colour, consistency or&nbsp;with strong smell.</li>
	<li>Unusual urine colour, smell or&nbsp;consistency; mucus, blood or&nbsp;pus in&nbsp;the urine.</li>
	<li>Decreased libido.</li>
	<li>Erectile and/or ejaculation disorders.</li>
</ul>
<h3>What to&nbsp;expect from a&nbsp;visit to&nbsp;your urologist-andrologist?</h3>
<p>
	 During your initial consultation, the doctor will listen to&nbsp;your complaints and ask questions to&nbsp;complete your case history. The questions will be&nbsp;about your general health, possible inherited and chronic disease, your sexual life. The examination may include abdominal, back and kidney area palpation, visual check of&nbsp;external genitalia, prostate rectal exam.
</p>
<p>
	 If&nbsp;necessary, our urologist-andrologist will ask you to&nbsp;do&nbsp;additional tests to&nbsp;evaluate your health condition and make a&nbsp;diagnosis. Depending on&nbsp;your symptoms, the additional tests may be&nbsp;laboratory (blood, urine, semen analyses, cytology, and histology tests) or&nbsp;instrumental (cystoscopy, Х-ray, ultrasound, CT, MRI). Based on&nbsp;the test results the doctor will make his conclusion and prescribe treatment for you.
</p>
<p>
	 The ICRM urologists have many years of&nbsp;work experience. Please, use our <a href="#contactus" data-modal-open="">contact form</a> to&nbsp;make an&nbsp;appointment. Our International Manager will contact you to&nbsp;offer convenient date and time. You can also make an&nbsp;appointment for the online consultation. However, please, remember that an&nbsp;online consultation cannot be&nbsp;equal to&nbsp;actually seeing a&nbsp;doctor.
