\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:0:{}}s:6:"action";b:0;}i:3943;a:86:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"3943";s:4:"NAME";s:19:"Breast Consultation";s:4:"CODE";s:19:"breast-consultation";s:12:"PREVIEW_TEXT";s:0:"";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:2236:"<p>
	 The professional area of&nbsp;the breast doctor includes:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Inflammatory breast disease (mastitis)</li>
	<li>Hormonal disorders (gynecomastia, mastopathy)</li>
	<li>Breast neoplasms (benign and malignant)</li>
	<li>Breast trauma consequences.</li>
	<li>Breast abnormalities, hypertrophy, asymmetry.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 Breast doctor consultation can also be&nbsp;necessary for men though this happens much less often compared to&nbsp;women.
</p>
<p>
	 Please, make an&nbsp;appointment with our breast doctor if&nbsp;you have one or&nbsp;of&nbsp;the following symptoms:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Breast deformation, asymmetry.</li>
	<li>Skin redness.</li>
	<li>Palpable lumps and/or nodes.</li>
	<li>Breast pains.</li>
	<li>Nipple retraction or&nbsp;swollen areolas.</li>
	<li>Nipple discharge without being pregnant or&nbsp;breastfeeding.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 The symptoms listed above require immediate consultation of&nbsp;a&nbsp;breast doctor. It&nbsp;would be&nbsp;better to&nbsp;visit a&nbsp;doctor in&nbsp;the period from day 6&nbsp;to&nbsp;12&nbsp;of&nbsp;your menstrual cycle.
</p>
<h2>What to&nbsp;expect from a&nbsp;visit to&nbsp;your breast doctor?</h2>
<p>
	 Our doctor will listen to&nbsp;your complaints, ask questions about your general health, possible previous diseases, your menstrual cycle and the contraceptives you might use. After the physical examination of&nbsp;your breasts, the doctor might ask you to&nbsp;do&nbsp;additional tests that could be&nbsp;the following:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>cancer-specific marker screening;</li>
	<li>ultrasound;</li>
	<li>mammography;</li>
	<li>ductography;</li>
	<li>CT;</li>
	<li>MRI;</li>
	<li>cytology evaluation of&nbsp;the nipple discharge;</li>
	<li>cyst or&nbsp;lump puncture;</li>
	<li>breast tissue biopsy.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 Please, use our <a href="#contactus" data-modal-open="">contact form</a> to&nbsp;make an&nbsp;appointment. Our international manager will contact you to&nbsp;offer convenient date and time.
</p>
<p>
	 You can also get an&nbsp;online consultation of&nbsp;the breast doctor. However, please, remember that an&nbsp;online consultation cannot be&nbsp;equal to&nbsp;actually seeing a&nbsp;doctor.
</p>
