	 In&nbsp;2005, the first Russian IVF program with frozen donor eggs was performed in&nbsp;ICRM. All donor oocytes (eggs) are frozen and stored in&nbsp;our cryobank according to&nbsp;the requirements of&nbsp;the Russian Law. The success rates in&nbsp;frozen donor egg cycles are similar to&nbsp;those in&nbsp;fresh cycles if&nbsp;no&nbsp;fewer than 9&nbsp;frozen oocytes are thawed.
</p>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:82:"/services/donorship-and-surrogacy/ivf-with-frozen-donor-eggs-from-icrm-donor-bank/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"186";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:957:"&lt;p&gt;In&nbsp;those cases where it&nbsp;is&nbsp;impossible to&nbsp;retrieve any oocytes for fertilization from a&nbsp;patient, our specialists can offer frozen donor eggs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advantages and specificities of&nbsp;an&nbsp;IVF protocol with frozen donor eggs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;wide choice of&nbsp;biomaterial from the ICRM cryobank;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;there is&nbsp;no&nbsp;need to&nbsp;wait until your donor is&nbsp;ready for ovarian stimulation and her follicles are grown and prepared for eggs retrieval;&lt;/li&gt;
