;s:15:"for all embryos";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:514:"<p>
	 Due to&nbsp;such structural chromosomal defects, a&nbsp;baby with congenital disorders may be&nbsp;born or&nbsp;an&nbsp;embryo may stop its development.
</p>
<h3>Indications for PGT-SR</h3>
<p>
	 The test is indicated when both or one of the parents is a carrier of a similar genetic abnormality.
</p>
<p>
	 The procedure is&nbsp;performed in&nbsp;two stages: the preparatory and the main one. In&nbsp;ICRM, we&nbsp;use tests with the maximum possible coverage and accuracy in&nbsp;the results.
</p>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:91:"/services/genetic-tests/pgt-for-chromosome-structural-rearrangement-carriers-7-chromosomes/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"185";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:596:"&lt;p&gt;PGT-SR is&nbsp;preimplantation genetic testing designed for carriers of&nbsp;chromosomal rearrangements, i.e.&nbsp;it&nbsp;detects a&nbsp;specific chromosomal structural rearrangement in&nbsp;an&nbsp;embryo. The test is&nbsp;aimed at&nbsp;understanding the structure of&nbsp;chromosomes involved. Structural chromosomal rearrangements can result&nbsp;in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;loss of&nbsp;genetic material;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;duplication of&nbsp;chromosome segments;&lt;/li&gt;
