<p>
	 Blastocyst (trophoblast) biopsy allows diagnosing an&nbsp;embryo before its implantation and transferring a&nbsp;healthy embryo into the uterus. The advantage of&nbsp;the procedure is&nbsp;in&nbsp;the fact that several cells can be&nbsp;collected, which increases accuracy of&nbsp;the laboratory test. Another advantage is&nbsp;that the probability of&nbsp;embryo damage is&nbsp;extremely low. Our embryologists has large experience in&nbsp;the procedure of&nbsp;trophoblast biopsy.
