_VALUE";s:5:"# ₽";s:24:"PROPERTY_FORMAT_VALUE_ID";s:7:"1048:97";s:24:"PROPERTY_DEC_POINT_VALUE";s:1:".";s:27:"PROPERTY_DEC_POINT_VALUE_ID";s:8:"1048:110";s:32:"PROPERTY_THOUSANDS_VARIANT_VALUE";s:1:" ";s:35:"PROPERTY_THOUSANDS_VARIANT_VALUE_ID";s:8:"1048:111";s:23:"PROPERTY_DECIMALS_VALUE";s:1:"2";s:26:"PROPERTY_DECIMALS_VALUE_ID";s:8:"1048:112";s:24:"PROPERTY_HIDE_ZERO_VALUE";s:1:"1";s:27:"PROPERTY_HIDE_ZERO_VALUE_ID";s:8:"1048:113";s:4:"SORT";s:3:"500";}s:5:"text1";s:0:"";s:5:"text2";s:0:"";s:5:"text3";s:0:"";s:10:"advantages";a:0:{}s:13:"disadvantages";a:0:{}s:12:"serviceTypes";O:29:"Illuminate\\Support\\Collection":1:{s:8:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'items";a:0:{}}s:6:"action";b:0;}}}i:184;a:25:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"184";s:4:"NAME";s:16:"Cryopreservation";s:4:"CODE";s:16:"cryopreservation";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2832";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:158:"Cryopreservation programs: sperm, eggs and embryos freezing and storage in our own cryobank - a safe way to keep your cells viable for future frozen transfers";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:27:"/services/cryopreservation/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"40";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-6";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"0";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:2364:"&lt;h2&gt;What is&nbsp;cryopreservation?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cryopreservation is&nbsp;one of&nbsp;the methods of&nbsp;assisted reproduction. Its main purpose is&nbsp;to&nbsp;preserve high-quality, viable embryos, male and female gametes by&nbsp;means of&nbsp;cooling them to&nbsp;very low temperatures. Fast freezing or&nbsp;vitrification&nbsp;&mdash; one of&nbsp;cryopreservation techniques&nbsp;&mdash; helps to&nbsp;prevent ice crystals formation and increase survival rate of&nbsp;the frozen biomaterial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;When is&nbsp;cryopreservation used?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Freezing may be&nbsp;initiated by&nbsp;a&nbsp;patient or&nbsp;recommended by&nbsp;a&nbsp;fertility specialist. The procedure allows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;preserving genetic material for a&nbsp;postponed pregnancy to&nbsp;reduce the risk of&nbsp;genetic defects in&nbsp;a&nbsp;future baby;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;increasing success rate in&nbsp;IVF programs;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;preserving fertility after chemotherapy of&nbsp;cancer tumors, removal of&nbsp;ovaries, or&nbsp;in&nbsp;the cases of&nbsp;early menopause;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;using biomaterial in&nbsp;gamete donation and surrogacy treatment programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is&nbsp;the effect of&nbsp;cryopreservation on&nbsp;embryos and gametes?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The most sensitive to&nbsp;freezing are oocytes (eggs). They badly tolerate changes in&nbsp;the environment. Functional abilities of&nbsp;all kinds of&nbsp;biomaterial do&nbsp;not change or&nbsp;even improve a&nbsp;little after thawing. The period of&nbsp;storage may be&nbsp;unlimited but, in&nbsp;average, it&nbsp;is&nbsp;from 5&nbsp;to&nbsp;15&nbsp;years. The cost of&nbsp;freezing depends on&nbsp;the type of&nbsp;biological material and the cryopreservation method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The International Centre for Reproductive Medicine (ICRM) offers cryopreservation services in&nbsp;Saint-Petersburg including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;sperm freezing;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;eggs and embryos vitrification;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;storage of&nbsp;biomaterial;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;thawing after eggs and embryos vitrification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The specialists of&nbsp;our Centre work to&nbsp;help every couple that addressed&nbsp;us achieve happy parenthood.&lt;/p&gt;";s:13:"actions_count";i:1;s:10:"prices_url";s:44:"/prices-and-actions/prices/#cryopreservation";s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:27:"/upload/iblock/c43/crio.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:50:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c43/0_0_1_95/crio.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:27:"/upload/iblock/c43/crio.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:54:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c43/114_114_1_95/crio.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:27:"/upload/iblock/c43/crio.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:54:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c43/114_114_1_95/crio.webp";s:8:"category";s:27:"/upload/iblock/c43/crio.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:54:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c43/114_114_1_95/crio.webp";s:6:"prices";s:27:"/upload/iblock/c43/crio.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:54:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c43/114_114_1_95/crio.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:0;s:8:"services";a:4:{i:4031;a:86:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"4031";s:4:"NAME";s:30:"Eggs and Embryos Vitrification";s:4:"CODE";s:30:"eggs-and-embryos-vitrification";s:12:"PREVIEW_TEXT";s:7:"1 straw";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:1616:"<h2>In&nbsp;what cases is&nbsp;cryopreservation of&nbsp;embryos/oocytes used?</h2>
<p>
	 An&nbsp;IVF treatment program usually involves hormonal ovarian stimulation to&nbsp;get not one (as&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;natural menstrual cycle) but more oocytes. As&nbsp;a&nbsp;result of&nbsp;their fertilization, embryologists receive several embryos, of&nbsp;which 1-2 best quality ones are transferred into the uterine cavity. The rest of&nbsp;the embryos can be&nbsp;frozen. Frozen/thawed embryos may be&nbsp;transferred later if&nbsp;a&nbsp;«fresh» transfer failed, or&nbsp;if&nbsp;a&nbsp;couple wants more children. Using frozen embryos helps to&nbsp;avoid new stimulated IVF cycle with more hormonal treatment and another eggs retrieval procedure.
</p>
<p>
	 Oocyte freezing is&nbsp;used in&nbsp;the following cases:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Social Freezing&nbsp;— a&nbsp;patient is&nbsp;collecting oocytes for their use in&nbsp;the future when she is&nbsp;ready for pregnancy;</li>
	<li>Fertility Preservation&nbsp;— a&nbsp;patient wants to&nbsp;freeze her oocytes before radiation or&nbsp;chemotherapy that can have a&nbsp;negative effect on&nbsp;her ovaries;</li>
	<li>if&nbsp;the oocytes cannot be&nbsp;fertilized for some reason, i.e.&nbsp;a&nbsp;partner was not able to&nbsp;collect his sperm or&nbsp;no&nbsp;sperm cells were found in&nbsp;his ejaculate;</li>
	<li>donor eggs freezing for future use in&nbsp;egg donation IVF treatment programs;</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 The ICRM IVF lab has highly qualified specialists and the latest equipment and reagents for the effective eggs and embryos vitrfication.
</p>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:58:"/services/cryopreservation/eggs-and-embryos-vitrification/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"184";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:945:"&lt;p&gt;Eggs and embryos cryopreservation means preserving biomaterial by&nbsp;cooling it&nbsp;to&nbsp;a&nbsp;very low temperature (-196&deg;С) using liquid nitrogen. At&nbsp;such low temperature, all biochemical processes inside the cells are effectively stopped, which allows using the frozen cells in&nbsp;months and years after their freezing. ICRM uses vitrification method for eggs and embryos. Firstly, the cells are treated with special media with cryoprotectors&nbsp;&mdash; substances that protect cells during the processes of&nbsp;freezing and thawing. Then oocytes/embryos are placed on&nbsp;a&nbsp;cryo-carrier and immediately immersed into liquid nitrogen. The cryo-carrier contains&nbsp;ID information of&nbsp;the patient: full name, medical record number, date of&nbsp;freezing, number of&nbsp;oocytes/embryos. After thawing, the oocytes/embryos are fully prepared for fertilization/transfer into the uterine cavity.&lt;/p&gt;";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}s:31:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:428";s:21:"PROPERTY_STAGES_VALUE";a:0:{}s:26:"PROPERTY_SPECIALISTS_VALUE";a:0:{}s:26:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_FULL_VALUE";s:10:"12 000 ₽";s:29:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_FULL_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:431";s:33:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";N;s:36:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:432";s:26:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_FULL_VALUE";N;s:29:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_FULL_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:433";s:33:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";N;s:36:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:434";s:23:"PROPERTY_CURRENCY_VALUE";N;s:26:"PROPERTY_CURRENCY_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:435";s:29:"PROPERTY_SHOW_ON_PRICES_VALUE";N;s:32:"PROPERTY_SHOW_ON_PRICES_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:436";s:28:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_ACTION_VALUE";N;s:31:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_ACTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4031:437";s:28:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_ACTI