	 Sperm cryopreservation is&nbsp;also possible if&nbsp;a&nbsp;man cannot be&nbsp;in&nbsp;the clinic on&nbsp;the day of&nbsp;his partner’s follicular puncture and eggs retrieval.
</p>
<h2>Sperm freezing procedure</h2>
<p>
	 Before sperm collection, a&nbsp;man does tests for infections, such as&nbsp;HIV, syphilis, hepatitis&nbsp;B and C.&nbsp;Ejaculate is&nbsp;collected by&nbsp;masturbation in&nbsp;a&nbsp;special room. It&nbsp;is&nbsp;placed in&nbsp;a&nbsp;labelled sterile container, which is&nbsp;then transferred to&nbsp;the laboratory. A&nbsp;lab specialist studies and describes the biomaterial according to&nbsp;certain parametres (volume, sperm cells concentration, their motility). After that, all collected sperm will be&nbsp;frozen.
</p>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:42:"/services/cryopreservation/sperm-freezing/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"184";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:526:"&lt;p&gt;Sperm freezing helps to&nbsp;preserve biological material for its future use in&nbsp;IVF treatment programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are indications for the procedure:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;hazardous job associated with the risk of&nbsp;male infertility;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;expected genital surgery;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;expected radiation or&nbsp;chemotherapy;&lt;/li&gt;
