<h3></h3>
<div>
	 Within IVF treatment programs, frozen biomaterial from cryobank is often used. Eggs, embryos and sperm are frozen and sent for storage in the following cases:&nbsp; <br>
	<ul>
		<li>to create bank of donor cells;&nbsp; </li>
		<li>if more eggs than necessary for an IVF program are retrieved after hormonal ovarian stimulation;</li>
		<li>&nbsp;if after embryo transfer good quality embryos are left;</li>
		<li>&nbsp;social freezing;</li>
		<li>for fertility preservation in those having occupational hazards, military personnel, cancer patients, etc.</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Conditions of cryo-storage of embryos, sperm and eggs</h3>
 </span> The carriers with frozen oocytes/ embryos/ sperm are placed into special holders located in the Dewar flasks – these are special containers filled with liquid nitrogen or nitrogen vapor. The temperature in them is very low, - 196C, which is necessary to store biological material safely. We use a special control system of nitrogen level in the Dewar flasks.&nbsp;<br>
 In order to avoid any possible mistakes, all carriers of frozen biomaterial are marked with patients’ full name, medical chart numbers, and dates of freezing. The location of every carrier is recorded both in a printed and an electronic storage registries. So, to find a required carrier is not a problem. Frozen embryos, sperm and eggs can be stored for unlimited time.&nbsp;<br>
