:"Laparoscopic Surgery";s:4:"CODE";s:20:"laparoscopic-surgery";s:12:"PREVIEW_TEXT";s:131:"A highly informative and less traumatic method of surgery that allows manipulations through small incisions under video control<br>";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:2307:"<h3>
There are three types of laparoscopy:<br>
 </h3>
 Diagnostic laparoscopy is performed to better understand the causes of infertility by visual inspection of abdominal and pelvic organs. It includes thorough evaluation of internal reproductive organs: the uterus, the ovaries, the fallopian tubes patency check is mandatory. Peritoneum inspection allows to diagnose endometriosis. If any problems revealed (endometriosis, uterine fibroid, ovarian cyst, adhesions) surgical treatment will be performed there and then.<br>
 <br>
 Operative laparoscopy is performed to treat gynecological diseases (endometriosis, uterine fibroid, ovarian cyst, hydrosalpinx).<br>
 <br>
 Review laparoscopy is performed to check the effectiveness of earlier surgical interventions.<br>
 <br>
<h2></h2>
<h2>Medical indications for diagnostic and treatment laparoscopy</h2>
<h3>
Planned laparoscopies: </h3>
<ul>
	<li>tumors, uterine fibroids, polyps, adhesions and other disorders in&nbsp;the uterus, its adnexa and ovaries;</li>
	<li>ovarian or&nbsp;peritoneal endometriosis;</li>
	<li>tuboperitoneal infertility;</li>
	<li>abnormal structure of&nbsp;internal reproductive organs;</li>
	<li>pelvic pains of&nbsp;uncertain origin.</li>
</ul>
<h3>
Emergency laparoscopies: </h3>
<ul>
	<li>acute pelvic inflammation;</li>
	<li>ectopic pregnancy;</li>
	<li>ovariorrhexis;</li>
	<li>suspected fibroid torsion or&nbsp;rupture of&nbsp;the ovarian tumor;</li>
	<li>a&nbsp;necessity to&nbsp;exclude gynecologic pathology when diagnosing an&nbsp;acute surgical condition.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Preparation before diagnostic or&nbsp;treatment laparoscopy</h3>
<p>
	 In&nbsp;the case of&nbsp;a&nbsp;planned surgical treatment, you doctor will administer a&nbsp;number of&nbsp;tests.
</p>
<ul>
	<li>lab tests: urinalysis, clinical and biochemical blood tests, coagulation test, smear flora test, etc.;</li>
	<li>pelvic ultrasound;</li>
	<li>colposcopy;</li>
	<li>ECG, etc.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 By&nbsp;the day of&nbsp;surgical treatment, the patient must have valid results of&nbsp;fluorography (or&nbsp;chest X-ray), breast ultrasound (or&nbsp;mammography). You doctor will give you all necessary referrals as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;recommendations about your diet and possible intake of&nbsp;medications.
</p>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:52:"/services/reproductive-surgery/laparoscopic-surgery/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"183";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:477:"&lt;p&gt;In&nbsp;Gynecology, laparoscopy is&nbsp;used as&nbsp;a&nbsp;minimally invasive alternative to&nbsp;classical surgery. It&nbsp;is&nbsp;an&nbsp;endoscopic diagnostic and treatment procedure. Manipulations are performed with the help of&nbsp;thin tube ended in&nbsp;a&nbsp;small video camera (endoscope). The tube as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;micro instruments are introduced through one or&nbsp;more small incisions up&nbsp;to&nbsp;10mm in&nbsp;an&nbsp;abdominal wall.&lt;/p&gt;";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}s:31:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4013:428";s:21:"PROPERTY_STAGES_VALUE";a:4:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:10:"Anesthesia";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}i:1;a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:143:"Through small incisions made on the tummy, gas is insufflated into the abdominal cavity, then a camera and surgical instruments are introduced.";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}i:2;a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:240:"Pelvic organs inspection. Evaluation of the uterus, the ovaries, the peritoneum, check of the fallopian tubes patency.  If any pathology revealed, surgical treatment is performed (cyst or uterine fibroid removal, separation of commissures).";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}i:3;a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:101:"Removal of the instruments, the gas, and the camera, post-operative treatment of the surgical wounds.";s:4:"TYPE";s:4:"HTML";}}s:26:"PROPERTY_SPECIALISTS_VALUE";a:2:{i:0;s:2:"27";i:1;s:2:"50";}s:26:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_FULL_VALUE";s:15:"from 30 000 ₽";s:29:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_FULL_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4013:431";s:33:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";N;s:36:"PROPERTY_PRICE1_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4013:432";s:26:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_FULL_VALUE";N;s:29:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_FULL_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4013:433";s:33:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";N;s:36:"PROPERTY_PRICE2_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:8:"4013:434";s:23:"PROPERTY_CURRENCY_VALUE";N;s: