</ul>
<h2>Advantages of&nbsp;hysteroscopy </h2>
<p>
	 The benefits of&nbsp;the technique are the following:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>minimal invasion (though the procedure is&nbsp;considered surgical, no&nbsp;sutures are necessary);</li>
	<li>high informative value;</li>
	<li>low risk of&nbsp;complications (bleeding, inflammation, etc.);</li>
	<li>an&nbsp;opportunity to&nbsp;perform visual evaluation and treatment simultaneously.</li>
</ul>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:44:"/services/reproductive-surgery/hysteroscopy/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"183";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:953:"&lt;p&gt;
	 Hysteroscopy is&nbsp;a&nbsp;minimally invasive surgery performed for treatment and diagnostic purposes. A&nbsp;hysteroscope is&nbsp;introduced through the vagina. This mini video camera translates a&nbsp;20-times magnified image on&nbsp;a&nbsp;screen that allows visual assessment of&nbsp;the cervical canal and the uterine cavity condition. The procedure may include endometrial biopsy or&nbsp;separate diagnostic curettage of&nbsp;the uterus. Hysteroresectoscopy (operative hysteroscopy) is&nbsp;different from hysteroscopy as&nbsp;in&nbsp;addition to&nbsp;the video camera another tool is&nbsp;used&nbsp;— a&nbsp;hysteroresectoscope&nbsp;— to&nbsp;perform various surgical operations (polyp removal, uterine anomalies correction).
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 Office hysteroscopy (diagnostic hysteroscopy) is&nbsp;a&nbsp;procedure using the minimal size of&nbsp;hysteroscope, which makes it&nbsp;painless without anesthesia.
