<p>
	 The procedure is&nbsp;done under intravenous anesthesia and in&nbsp;average lasts for up&nbsp;to&nbsp;25&nbsp;minutes. This is&nbsp;often performed at&nbsp;the same time as&nbsp;a&nbsp;hysteroscopy. The recovery is&nbsp;fast&nbsp;— a&nbsp;woman can get back to&nbsp;her normal routine on&nbsp;the next day. Nevertheless, your doctor may instruct you to&nbsp;avoid use of&nbsp;tampons or&nbsp;avoid sexual intercourse for 7-10&nbsp;days. The procedure is&nbsp;considered to&nbsp;be&nbsp;minor. In&nbsp;ICRM, experienced gynecologists will perform it&nbsp;as&nbsp;carefully as&nbsp;possible to&nbsp;minimize the risks for the patient.
