	 A method of&nbsp;uterine fibroid surgical treatment. The operation is&nbsp;aimed at&nbsp;removal of&nbsp;the tumor(s) without damaging the surrounding tissues of&nbsp;the uterus and other reproductive organs.
</p>
<p>
	 The surgery can be transvaginal or transabdominal. The transvaginal approach allows removing cervical fibroids as well as myomectomy and hystero-resectoscopy of the nodes. The transabdominal approach includes laparotomy and laparoscopy. The choice of the method and scope of the surgery depends on a number of factors: organ size, its motility, a possibility of other organs compression, number and location of the nodes, co-morbidities, etc.
