2:"91";s:20:"PROPERTY_PRICE_VALUE";s:5:"3 000";s:23:"PROPERTY_PRICE_VALUE_ID";s:9:"45512:439";s:32:"PROPERTY_PRICE_DESCRIPTION_VALUE";N;s:35:"PROPERTY_PRICE_DESCRIPTION_VALUE_ID";s:9:"45512:440";s:4:"SORT";s:4:"1400";s:17:"PREVIEW_TEXT_TYPE";s:4:"text";}s:20:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'languageAccessors";a:0:{}s:7:"related";a:0:{}s:9:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'hidden";a:0:{}s:10:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'visible";a:0:{}}}}s:6:"action";b:0;}i:37357;a:86:{s:2:"ID";s:5:"37357";s:4:"NAME";s:18:"Endometrial Biopsy";s:4:"CODE";s:18:"endometrial-biopsy";s:12:"PREVIEW_TEXT";s:52:"A method to evaluate the state of the uterine lining";s:11:"DETAIL_TEXT";s:1393:"<p>
	There are several types of&nbsp;the endometrial biopsy:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Pipelle endometrial sampling is&nbsp;a&nbsp;modern version of&nbsp;the procedure using a&nbsp;less traumatic instrument&nbsp;— pipelle.</li>
	<li>Vacuum suction biopsy is&nbsp;performed with the help of&nbsp;a&nbsp;special syringe.</li>
	<li>Endometrial biopsy during office hysteroscopy is&nbsp;done with a&nbsp;special tool, it&nbsp;is&nbsp;painless and does not require anesthesia.</li>
	<li>Streak curretage is&nbsp;usually performed during hysteroscopy procedure under general anesthesia.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Advantages and specificities of&nbsp;endometrial biopsy</h3>
<ul>
	<li>the procedure is&nbsp;fast, sparing and possible for out-patients;</li>
	<li>it&nbsp;is&nbsp;practically painless, so&nbsp;anesthesia is&nbsp;not required;</li>
	<li>atraumatic intervention (without cervical canal widening);</li>
	<li>histologic confirmation of&nbsp;the diagnosis (a&nbsp;fragment of&nbsp;the uterine lining is&nbsp;examined under the microscope);</li>
	<li>low risk of&nbsp;post-procedure complications such as&nbsp;bleeding or&nbsp;inflammation;</li>
	<li>work capacity is&nbsp;not impaired. The procedure can be&nbsp;performed during hysteroscopy;</li>
</ul>
<p>
	In&nbsp;our Centre, the procedure is&nbsp;performed by&nbsp;experienced doctors, highly qualified obstetricians-gynecologists.
