<p>
	 The cyst aspiration is&nbsp;performed on&nbsp;the gynecological examination chair under local or&nbsp;general anesthesia. The procedure takes 10-15&nbsp;minutes. In&nbsp;the case of&nbsp;endometrioid ovarian cyst, your doctor may make a&nbsp;decision to&nbsp;remove&nbsp;it: after the fluid is&nbsp;withdrawn from the cyst, a&nbsp;special sclerotherapy solution will be&nbsp;injected to&nbsp;cause adherence of&nbsp;the cyst walls.
</p>
<p>
	 Possible indications for the cyst removal:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>a&nbsp;risk of&nbsp;rupture of&nbsp;the cavity filled with fluid;</li>
	<li>severe pain;</li>
	<li>the cyst size 16&nbsp;— 20&nbsp;mm and more and no&nbsp;result after the medication therapy.</li>
