 <br>
 Depending on its size, there are three types of the surgery:<br>
 <br>
<ul>
	<li>
	A <b>subtotal hysterectomy</b> or supracervical uterus amputation (the cervix is saved)</li>
	<li>
	A <b>total hysterectomy</b> (both the uterus and the cervix are removed)</li>
	<li>
	A <b>radical hysterectomy</b> (the uterus, cervix, both ovaries, and both fallopian tubes are removed).</li>
</ul>
 The operation can be performed using laparoscopy, laparotomy or transvaginal technique. A woman may have a hysterectomy for different reasons, including: uterine tumours like large and fast growing fibroids that cause pain, bleeding, or compression of other organs, uterine prolapse, adenomyosis that causes bleeding or anemia, ovarian, cervical or uterine cancer.<br>";s:15:"DETAIL_PAGE_URL";s:44:"/services/reproductive-surgery/hysterectomy/";s:17:"IBLOCK_SECTION_ID";s:3:"183";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:28:"PROPERTY_PARTICULARITY_VALUE";a:2:{s:4:"TEXT";s:308:"&lt;ul&gt;
